## Chapter 5: Nearer to the Heart's Desire

**Overview**: 1944 Bretton Woods meeting established **IMF** and **World Bank** to eliminate gold from world finance; hidden agenda was building world socialism; Federal Reserve's role in enabling this.

### Bretton Woods: An Attack on Gold

- July 1944, Mount Washington Hotel, Bretton Woods, New Hampshire
- **United Nations Monetary and Financial Conference**
- Created two agencies:
  - **International Monetary Fund (IMF)**
  - **International Bank for Reconstruction and Development (World Bank)**

**Announced purposes**:

- World Bank: loans to war-torn/underdeveloped nations for economic development
- IMF: promote monetary cooperation, maintain fixed exchange rates

**Actual goal**: Terminate gold as basis of international currency, replace with politically manipulated paper standard — allow governments to escape gold discipline and create money without currency devaluation penalties

### Gold-Exchange Standard vs. Gold Standard

- Prior to Bretton Woods: **gold-exchange standard**
- Not same as gold-standard (currency backed by gold)
- Exchange ratios of currencies determined by gold market value (supply/demand)
- Politicians and bankers hated it — beyond their manipulation ability
- Strict disciplinarian mechanism

**John Kenneth Galbraith**: "The Bretton Woods arrangements sought to recapture the advantages of the gold standard — currencies that were exchangeable at stable and predictable rates into gold and thus at stable and predictable rates into each other. And this it sought to accomplish while minimizing the pain imposed by the gold standard on countries that were buying too much, selling too little and thus losing gold."

### The Plan: A World Central Bank

Method paralleled Jekyll Island plan for American banks:

- Create money out of nothing without currency devaluation by other banks
- **World central bank** creating common fiat money for all nations
- Require nations to inflate together at same rate
- International insurance fund to rush fiat money to any nation facing currency "run"

Plan architects:

- **John Maynard Keynes** (Fabian Socialist, England)
- **Harry Dexter White** (Assistant Secretary of US Treasury)

### The Fabian Society

**Elite intellectual group** with semi-secret society for bringing socialism to world:

- Preferred **gradual approach** (propaganda/legislation) vs. Communist violence/revolution
- Avoided word "socialism" — spoke of welfare, medical care, higher wages, better conditions
- Accomplished objectives without bloodshed or opposition
- Scorned Communists for methods, not goals
- **Turtle symbol** emphasized gradualism
- Early leaders: **Sidney and Beatrice Webb**, **George Bernard Shaw**

**Beatrice Webb House stained-glass window** (Surrey, England) — Omar Khayyam quote:

> "Dear love, couldst thou and I with fate conspire
> To grasp this sorry scheme of things entire,
> Would we not shatter it to bits, and then
> Remould it nearer to the heart's desire!"

- Mural depicts Shaw and Webb striking earth with hammers
- Masses kneel worshiping books advocating socialism
- **H.G. Wells** called them "the new machiavellians"
- **Fabian crest**: wolf in sheep's clothing

### Communist Moles

**Harry Dexter White**:

- America's chief technical expert and dominant force at conference
- Eventually became first Executive Director for US at IMF
- Member of **Council on Foreign Relations (CFR)**
- Member of Communist espionage ring in Washington
- Served as Assistant Secretary of Treasury
- **FBI informed White House** of his activities (Truman appointed him anyway)

**Virginius Frank Coe**:

- Technical secretary at Bretton Woods
- Same espionage ring as White
- Later became first Secretary of IMF

Hidden drama: **Fabian Socialists and Communists** were intellectual architects, though disagreeing on method, in perfect harmony on goal — **international socialism**.

### Why Communists Supported IMF/World Bank

Soviet Union didn't join, but supported creation because:

- Goal: world currency, world central bank, control economies of all nations
- Required US to surrender dominant position, be reduced to part of collective
- **World Bank** seen as vehicle to move capital from US/industrialized nations to underdeveloped nations controlled by Marxists
- Transfer wealth from West, eventually making developed nations pay developing nations' bills

### IMF Structure and Funding

- Appears to be part of UN (like Fed appears part of US government) but **entirely independent**
- Funded by quota from ~200 member nations
- Greatest capital from industrialized nations (Britain, Japan, France, Germany)
- **US contributes ~20%** but represents ~40% in reality (other nations contribute worthless currencies)
- World prefers dollars

**Routine operation**: exchange worthless currencies for dollars — kind of international FDIC rushing money to bankrupt countries to avoid currency devaluation

### Paper Gold: Special Drawing Rights (SDR)

- 1970: IMF created **SDR (Special Drawing Right)**
- Called "paper gold" but pure bookkeeping wizardry — no relation to gold
- Based on "credits" (promises governments will tax citizens if needed)
- IMF considers these "assets" that become "reserves" for loans to other governments
- **Dennis Turner**: "SDRs are turned into loans to Third-World nations by the creation of checking accounts in the commercial or central banks of the member nations in the name of the debtor governments.... The IMF creates dollars, francs, pounds, or other hard currencies and gives them to a Third-World dictator, with inflation resulting in the country where the currency originated.... Inflation is caused in the industrialized nations while wealth is transferred from the general public to the debtor country."

**Keynes' vision fulfilled**: world central bank issuing reserve currency ("bancor") to free governments from gold discipline

### Gold Finally Abandoned

- August 15, 1971: **Nixon ended dollar convertibility to gold**
- First phase of IMF metamorphosis complete
- Not yet true central bank (couldn't create own world currency)
- Depended on central banks of member nations for cash/credits
- Since these banks could create unlimited money, no limit from now on

**New goal post-gold**: "overcome trade deficits" (after abandoning fixed exchange rate mission)

### Trade Deficits

**Definition**: country imports greater value than exports — spends more than earns

Five ways to address unsustainable spending:

1. **Increase earnings** (only long-term solution) — requires free-enterprise system
2. **Take from savings** — most governments have none, debts exceed assets
3. **Sell assets** — most countries have few marketable assets (gold already drawn down)
4. **Borrow money** — where IMF positioned itself in 1970
5. **Counterfeit** — only US can do this (dollar is international medium)

### The Counterfeit Option

Only available if currency is accepted for international trade (US position):

- US spent more than earned by having Federal Reserve create whatever needed
- Post-1971, dollar competed with mark/yen on merit basis — value increasingly discounted
- Still preferred medium of exchange
- US safest investment destination
- Foreigners needed dollars to invest in US
- Despite Fed creating huge amounts, foreign demand seemingly limitless
- **America financed trade deficit with fiat money** — feat no other nation could accomplish

> "We have been told that our nation's trade deficit is a terrible... In truth, America is not hurt by a trade deficit at all.... We are the benefactors while our trading partners are the victims. We get the cars and TV sets while they get the funny money. We get the hardware. They get the paperware."

**Dark side**: When dollar tumbles and foreigners reject it, free ride ends — hundreds of billions held overseas will flood back, bidding up prices as foreigners convert to real estate/factories/products before further devaluation — **inflation postponed because foreigners took dollars out of economy**

**Ultimate cause**: Trade deficit could not have happened without Federal Reserve creating fiat money

### IMF Loans: Doomed But Sweet

- Loans go to **state-owned/state-operated industries** (bureaucracy, corruption)
- Doomed from start, consume loans with no repayment possibility
- Interest becomes unmanageable
- IMF falls back to "reserves" → "assets" → "credits" → eventually **taxpayers bail them out**

**World Bank** (sister organization):

- Lending agency to IMF's central banking function
- "Savior of the World" — aid underdeveloped nations, feed hungry, better life for mankind
- Provides loans at favorable terms (below market, 50-year terms, no payments for 10 years)
- Funding: small cash from members + promises (callable capital ~10x more) — FDIC-like insurance with no reserve fund
- Goes to commercial loan markets and borrows at low rates (backed by powerful governments forcing taxpayers to pay)

**Hidden cost**: money that would have been available for private sector investment/consumer loans — siphons development capital, prevents job creation, raises interest rates, retards economy

### The Hidden Agenda: World Socialism

World Bank perceived by founders **as instrument for social and political change** — building world socialism

Evidence in **Sectoral Loans and Structural-Adjustment Loans**:

- Sectoral: part for projects, rest for "policy changes in economic sector"
- Structural-Adjustment: all money for policy changes, none for projects
- Recent years: ~half of underdeveloped country loans in that category

**What policy changes?** → **Building world socialism**:

- Government hydro-electric projects
- Government oil refineries
- Government lumber mills
- Government mining companies
- Government steel plants
- Money from government, to government, administered by government → expansion of government

**Example loan condition**: recipient country must "hold down wages" — government must have power to set wages (omnipotent state)

**Paul Roberts** (William E. Simon Chair, Center for Strategic and International Studies):

> "The entire 'development process' has been guided by the belief that reliance on private enterprise and equity investment is incompatible with economic and social progress. In place of such proven avenues of success, development planning substituted loans and foreign aid so that governments of the LDCs [Less Developed Countries] could control economic activity in keeping with plans drawn up by experts.... economic life in the LDCs was politicized from the start."

**Ken Ewert**: "The Fund concentrates on 'macro-policies,' such as fiscal and monetary policies or exchange rates, and pays little attention to fundamental issues like private property rights and freedom of enterprise. Implicit... is the belief that with proper 'macro-management' any economic system is viable...."

> "Even more important, it has allowed governments the world over to expropriate the wealth of their citizens more efficiently (through the hidden tax of inflation) while at the same time aggrandizing their own power. There is little doubt that the IMF is an influence for world-wide socialism."

