### Structural-Adjustment Loans (SALs)

- **SALs don't require specific development projects** — money can be spent on anything the recipient government wishes, including interest payments on overdue commercial bank loans
- World Bank becomes a **conduit from taxpayers to commercial banks** that made risky Third-World loans
- The mechanism: taxpayer money flows to governments → governments pay interest to banks

