## Summary of Fiat Money System (pp. 241)

- American dollar has no intrinsic value — classic **fiat money** with unlimited production capacity
- Primary value lies in willingness of people to accept it, backed by **legal tender laws**
- Money created "out of nothing" but more accurately "based upon debt"
- **Entire money supply would vanish** if all debts were repaid
- Under Federal Reserve System, leaders cannot allow serious reduction in national or consumer debt
- **Mandrake Mechanism** converts debt into money — designed to confuse and deceive, not to be logical
- End product: **artificial expansion of money supply** → root cause of **hidden tax called inflation**
- Expansion leads to contraction, producing **destructive boom-bust cycle** throughout history wherever fiat money existed

## Key Financiers & Their Connections (pp. 241-244)

