- Morgans were friendly competitors with Rothschilds, became socially close
- Morgan's London-based firm **saved from financial ruin in 1857 by Bank of England** (Rothschilds held great influence)
- Thereafter, Morgan appears to have served as **Rothschild financial agent**
- Went to great length to appear totally American
- Initially made fortune in oil, then gravitated into banking and finance
