## Ruskin, Rhodes, and Milner

### John Ruskin's Philosophy

- **1870**: wealthy British socialist **John Ruskin** appointed professor of fine arts at **Oxford University**
- Taught: state must take control of means of production, organize for community good
- Advocated **small ruling class control**, perhaps even **single dictator**

> "My continual aim has been to show the eternal superiority of some men to others, sometimes even of one man to all others."

- Same intellectual appeal as Communism
- **Lenin** taught: masses can't be trusted, special group of disciplined intellectuals must assume control
- Function of **Communist Party** (never more than ~3% of population)
- Even with elections charade, **only Party members** (or KGB-controlled) can run for office
- This **ruling party/class ideal** = heart of all **collectivist schemes** (Socialism, Communism, Nazism, Fascism, or any "ism")
- Comfortable for adherents of elitist mentality in almost any collectivist camp

> "This network, which we may identify as the Round Table Groups, has no aversion to cooperating with the Communists, or any other groups, and frequently does so."

### Ruskin's Impact on Oxford

- Spoke to Oxford undergraduates as **privileged ruling class**
- Told them they possessed magnificent tradition (education, beauty, rule of law, freedom, decency, self-discipline)
- But tradition couldn't be saved unless **extended to lower classes in England and non-English throughout world**

### Cecil Rhodes' Fortune

- Ruskin's inaugural lecture **copied in long-hand** by undergraduate **Cecil Rhodes**, who kept it **thirty years**
- Rhodes made **world's greatest fortune** via diamond/gold monopoly (cooperation with **Bank of England** and **Rothschild**)
- Vast income spent to **advance ruling-class ideas of John Ruskin**

### Rhodes' Secret Society

- **Rhodes Scholarships** (established by seventh will) known to everyone
- **Not widely known**: Rhodes' **five previous wills** left fortune to **form secret society**
- Devoted to **preservation and expansion of British Empire**
- Secret society **created by Rhodes and Lord Milner**, **continues to exist** to this day
- **William T. Stead** (member of inner circle) wrote: "Mr. Rhodes was more than founder of dynasty. He aspired to be creator of one of those vast semi-religious, quasi-political associations which, like Society of Jesus, have played so large a part in history of world."

### Leadership Structure

- Rhodes: leader
- **Stead**, **Brett (Lord Esher)**, **Milner**: executive committee
- **Arthur (Lord) Balfour**, **(Sir) Harry Johnston**, **Lord Rothschild**, **Albert (Lord) Grey**: potential members of "**Circle of Initiates**"
- Outer circle: "**Association of Helpers**" (later organized by Milner as **Round Table organization**)

## The Pattern of Conspiracy

### Concentric Rings of Control

- Classical pattern of political conspiracy
- Structure enabling differentiation between **international "network"** and **secret society within that network**
- At center: **tiny group in complete control**, one man as undisputed leader
- Next: **circle of secondary leadership** (mostly unaware of inner core, led to believe they're inner-most ring)

### Building Outward

- Over time, conspiracies build **additional rings of organization**
- **Outer echelons** usually idealists with honest desire to improve world
- Never suspect inner control for other purposes
- Only ruthless few demonstrating capacity for higher leadership allowed to see it

### After Rhodes' Death

