- Wealthy associates: **Beit brothers**, **Sir Abe Bailey**, **Astor family** (after 1915)
- Foundations/firms associated with international banking fraternity: **Carnegie United Kingdom Trust**, organizations associated with **J.P. Morgan**, **Rockefeller and Whitney families**, associates of **Lazard Brothers** and **Morgan, Grenfell, and Company**

## Round Table Expansion and CFR

### Post-WWI Expansion

- End of **1914 war**: organization system had to be **greatly extended**
- Task entrusted to **Lionel Curtis**
- Established (in England and each dominion) **front organization** to existing local Round Table Group
- Front organization: **Royal Institute of International Affairs**
- Nucleus in each area: existing submerged Round Table Group
- In New York: **Council on Foreign Relations** (front for **J.P. Morgan and Company** in association with very small American Round Table Group)

### CFR Origins

- Spin-off from **failure of world leaders** to embrace **League of Nations** as true world government (end of WWI)
- Master planners unrealistic in expectations for rapid acceptance
- Plan required **patient gradualism** symbolized by **Fabian turtle**

### Rose Martin on Colonel House's Strategy

- **Colonel House** only one man, multitude needed
- Set pattern and outlined goals for future, still had scheme or two in mind
- Particular need: develop **top level Anglo-American planning group** in field of foreign relations to:
  - Secretly influence policy
  - Gradually "educate" public opinion

### Hotel Majestic Meeting (May 19, 1919)

- **Arnold Toynbee**, **R.H. Tawney**, **John Maynard Keynes** — all disillusioned by peace consequences
- Made **gentlemen's agreement** to set up organization with branches in England and America to "**facilitate scientific study of international questions**"
- Result: **two potent and closely related opinion-making bodies**:
  - English branch: **Royal Institute of International Affairs**
  - American branch: first **Institute of International Affairs**, reorganized 1921 as **Council on Foreign Relations**

### CFR Influence

- Through CFR and its influence over **media**, **tax-exempt foundations**, **universities**, **government agencies**, international financiers dominate **domestic and foreign policies of United States** ever since

## Round Table Agents in Russia

### British and American Agents Everywhere

- Prior to and during revolution, many **local observers, tourists, newsmen** reported British and American agents everywhere in Petrograd
- Providing **money for insurrection**
- Example: British agents seen handing out **25-rouble notes** to men at **Pavlovski regiment** just before it mutinied and sided with revolution

### Milner and Buchanan's Role

- Funding provided by **Milner**, channeled through **Sir George Buchanan** (British Ambassador to Russia)
- Repeat of ploy that worked so well for cabal in past
