### American Red Cross Cover

- American Round Table agents **didn't have diplomatic service cover**
- Had to be **more ingenious**
- Came **disguised as Red Cross officials** on humanitarian mission
- Group consisted almost entirely of **financiers, lawyers, accountants** from **New York banks and investment houses**
- **Simply overpowered American Red Cross** organization with large contributions, purchased franchise to operate in its name

### Professor Sutton on Red Cross Takeover

- **1910 Red Cross fund-raising campaign** for $2 million successful only because supported by wealthy New York City residents
- **J.P. Morgan himself contributed $100,000**
- **Henry P. Davison** (Morgan partner) was chairman of 1910 New York Fund-Raising Committee, later became chairman of **War Council of American Red Cross**
- Red Cross unable to cope with WWI demands, **effectively taken over by New York bankers**

