## The Transfusion Mechanism

### How the Mechanism Works

Commodities sold to Soviet bloc at **below-world-market prices** — even below what Americans pay:
- American taxpayers make up the difference (as with Lend-Lease)
- Soviets don't need money to buy goods
- American financial institutions, federal government, IMF, World Bank lend them the money
- Interest rates **below market** — requiring additional subsidy from American citizens
- Loans **guaranteed by U.S. government**
