### New Money

**Three Months Later — State of National Emergency:**
- President declared state of national emergency
- Treasury Secretary announced multilateral treaty ratified solving inflationary problems
- New world-wide monetary unit called **the Bancor**
- Name proposed by **John Maynard Keynes** at Bretton Woods Conference 1944
- Will restore commerce, stop inflation
- Man will have total control over economic destiny
- Money becomes servant instead of master

**Implementation:**
- U.S. agreed to accept Bancor as legal tender for all debts (public and private)
- Old money honored but phased out over three months
- Federal Reserve Notes no longer valid after transition
- Old money exchanged at banks: **one Bancor for five hundred dollars**
- All existing contracts/home mortgages converted at same ratio

**Backing the New Money:**
- IMF/World Bank backing with assets of the world
- Includes bonds from participating governments plus millions of acres of wilderness lands deposited into **UN "Environmental Bank"**
- National Parks and forests of U.S. added to reserves
