- No public memory of another way of life; older generation "eliminated"
- Schools and textbooks reframe past as "era of unbridled competition, selfishness, and injustice"
- Private possessions (automobiles, homes, shoes) derided as "wasted artifacts of decadent society"

### No Taxes, Inflation, or Depressions

- Citizens work directly or indirectly for government
- Wages paid via electronic transfer to government-regulated bank controlling all spending
- Large corporations appear privately owned but are "junior partners of government"—fully regulated, protected from failure
- Compensation determined by "technical usefulness" and "political rank"
- Taxes are "pleasantly low or non-existent"
- Government costs derived from **expansion of money supply and economic value of work battalions**

### Government Financing Mechanism

- Regional governments determine spending needs, sell bonds in open market
- **IMF/World Bank** acts as UN central bank, primary bond buyer
- Bank determines allowed spending per region via electronic transfer of "credits"
- Local governments draw on credits to pay bills without tax revenue needed
- In past, money supply increases caused immediate wage/price inflation—**no longer**
- Prices and wages now **controlled**; wage-price spiral "eliminated"
- Government trapped in its own mechanism: must give wage increases to keep workers happy, but cannot allow price increases
- Result: **wage-price spiral only delayed, not eliminated**; hidden inflation persists
- People still pay cost through "hidden taxation called inflation"

### Historical Inflation as Social Engineering

- Pre-New World Order: industrialized nations experienced disruptive inflation (exceeding 1000% annually)
- Inflation served strategic purpose: **destroyed public faith in national governments**, softened populations, made them accept radical institutional changes
- Paved way for The New World Order
- Now: extreme inflation would cause "public dissatisfaction and" resistance—unacceptable in new system
- Inflation **institutionalized at "modest" 5% per year**—"optimum level for generating revenue without causing public alarm"
- Everyone agrees 5% is "moderate"; forgotten that it compounds **forever**

### Mathematical Effect of Persistent 5% Inflation

- 5% devaluation applies to all previously saved money, not just new earnings
- After 1 year: dollar worth 95 cents
- After 2 years: reduced again by 5%, worth 90 cents
- **After 20 years: government confiscates 64% of career savings**
- **After 45 years: government takes 90% of lifetime savings**
- Earned interest only partially offsets effect; does not alter "underlying reality of government confiscation"

### Control of Economic Cycles and Profit

- **No business cycles any longer**—inflation was the only hidden taxation mechanism; now price/wage controls prevent cycles
- No speculation possible (no funds to speculate with)
- No inventory expansion to maximize future profits (inventories determined by formula)
- **Profits determined by formula** and guaranteed, just large enough to keep pace with inflation
- **Chaos in economy now impossible**—not tolerated; neither are depressions
- Government releases statistics showing economy "steadily improving," though millions live in extreme hardship
- Starvation, work battalions in makeshift barracks, old buildings falling from lack of maintenance—but **officially "problems" are now illegal**
- Housing shortage officially "eliminated" (reclassified)

## Chapter Twenty-Five: A Realistic Scenario

### The Pessimistic Narrative Problem

- Pessimistic scenario discourages action; no one wants to hear it, even if true
- **Adlai Stevenson**: "The contest between agreeable fancy and disagreeable fact is unequal. Americans are suckers for good news"
- Author acknowledges: "If you want optimistic scenario, you're wasting time on this book"
- No optimistic scenario exists; events have progressed too far for reversal

### Why Events Cannot Be Reversed

- Even if Congress forced spending cuts, debt reduction, UN treaty disengagement, **the Cabal will not surrender without fight**
- Historical precedent: **Second Bank of the United States (1834)** under **Nicholas Biddle**
- Biddle deliberately caused economic chaos to discredit President Jackson's anti-bank policies
- Tightened credit, withdrew money from circulation, triggered full-scale depression
- Biddle declared: "All other banks and all the merchants may break, but the Bank of the United States shall not break"
- Current Federal Reserve has "infinitely greater" power to cause devastation than Biddle possessed
- "No one is going to get out of this one unscathed. There is hell to pay, and it is we who are going to pay it"

### Seventh Reason to Abolish the Federal Reserve

- **Federal Reserve is the starting point** of pessimistic scenario
- Chain of causation: fiat money (central bank) → government debt → inflation → economic destruction → poverty → excuse for increased government power → totalitarianism
- **Eliminate the Federal Reserve from this equation, and pessimistic scenario ceases to exist**
- Seventh and final reason to abolish the Fed: **it is an instrument of totalitarianism**

### The Middle Ground: Realism

- Between optimism and pessimism lies **realism**
- Realistic scenario ≠ predetermined, nor even likely—realistic only if certain conditions are met
- Balance of chapter devoted to analysis of those conditions

### What Must Not Be Done

- Must **not turn to government** for "cures" that created the problem
- Do not want more power to Fed, Treasury, or President
- Probably don't need new laws (except repeals of old ones)
- Goal: **reduction of government, not expansion**

- **Do not abolish Fed and transfer to Treasury**—popular among Populists and Social Credit advocates
- False argument: Federal Reserve is private, independent; Congress authorized to issue nation's money
- Reality: only Congress authorized to issue currency; letting Treasury issue it (instead of bankers) solves nothing
- If Fed abolished, Treasury would still create fiat money via bond sales to central bank
- **Same result, different mechanism**: inflation and debt accumulation continue endlessly

<!-- pp. 641-660 -->

### Fed Ownership Myth: Neither Private Nor Government

- **Claim that Fed is privately owned is "legal fiction"** — member banks hold stock, but it carries no voting weight; stock can't be sold or traded
- Stockholders have none of the usual elements of control — subservient to Board of Governors (7 members appointed by President, confirmed by Senate)
- **True nature: Fed is a hybrid** — association of large commercial banks granted special privileges by Congress
- More accurate description: **"a cartel protected by federal law"**
- **Ownership structure irrelevant to function** — even if entirely private, same people would run it, same money creation for political purposes
- Bank of England precedent: privately owned at inception, became official arm of British government later; function unchanged
- Central banks of industrialized nations are government arms — indistinguishable in function from the Fed

### A Realistic Scenario: Why Simply Ending the Fed Won't Work

- Terminating interest payments would hurt millions with insurance policies, investments, retirement plans — Social Credit scheme would "wipe out the economy in one fell swoop"
- **Deep problem remains**: politicians would stay even if bankers are cut out; Congress acting as central bank would continue expanding money supply, inflation would roar
- Issuing money without gold/silver backing **violates the Constitution**

### The JFK Rumor

- **1981 rumor**: Kennedy assassinated by "hidden money power" for signing Executive Order #11110 instructing Treasury to print $4+ billion in United States Notes
- **Rumor was wrong on multiple counts**:
  - Order involved Silver Certificates (backed by silver), not United States Notes
  - No interest paid on Silver Certificates either, so bankers wouldn't lose interest income
  - **Order didn't instruct Treasury to issue Silver Certificates** — merely authorized it; no evidence Certificates were printed
  - 1987: Reagan rescinded the order
- Treasury did print United States Notes in 1963, authorized by 1878 act replacing Civil War Greenbacks; JFK didn't initiate that issue
- Greatest quantity in circulation since 1969: $322 million — insignificant compared to Federal Reserve Notes
- **Columbia University speech quote**: books claimed Kennedy warned "high office of President has been used to foment a plot to destroy Americans' freedom" ten days before assassination
  - Columbia University confirmed Kennedy **never spoke there** — not ten days before nor at any other time
  - **Ronald Whealan** (head librarian, JFK Library): "Ten days prior to the assassination he was at the White House meeting with... the ambassador to the United States from Portugal"
- Kennedy had been **lifelong socialist and internationalist** — attended Fabian London School of Economics, participated in destroying American money supply, engineered transfer of wealth to foreign nations
- Little reason to believe he had "seen the light" and was reversing life-long beliefs

### Monetarists vs Supply-Siders

- **Monetarists** (Milton Friedman): money created by Mandrake Mechanism, but supply determined by strict formula established by Congress, not Fed
- **Supply-siders** (Arthur Laffer, Charles Kadlec): formulas also, but different — money supply determined by current demand for gold ("gold-price rule")
- Not true gold standard — just observe gold price, tinker with dollar by expanding/contracting money supply to keep relative value constant
- **Common ground**: both groups share faith in politically-created formulas, bureaus, agencies; free market won't work without assistance
- Fed remains unscathed as "ultimate mechanism for intervention" — these groups just want their turn running it

### Jerry Jordan's National Lottery Proposal (1989)

- **Jerry Jordan** suggested expanding monetary base by holding national lottery — government pays out more dollars in prize money than ticket sales
- Excess payout = amount by which monetary base expands
- Jordan acknowledged: **"there would not be any effective institutional restraint on the growth of the monetary base"** — same problem with all schemes involving monetary control by men

### Balanced-Budget Amendment

- **Not the answer — an illusion and fraud**
- Biggest spenders in Congress support it — popular with voters but wouldn't cramp spending style
- If not permitted to spend more than tax receipts, perfect excuse for raising taxes — way to punish voters for placing limits
- Most versions have **escape hatch**: "except in cases of emergency" — Congress decides what constitutes emergency
- **Serious amendment would limit spending, not balance budget** — but given current Congressional composition, better to throw big spenders out of office
- Another flaw: **doesn't affect off-budget expenditures (entitlements)** — now 52% of federal outlays, growing 12% yearly
- Even if Congress stopped deficit spending, **balanced-budget amendment wouldn't solve inflation or national debt** — Fed can inflate using literally any debt in the world

### Auditing the Fed: Exercise in Futility

- Congressional bills to investigate/audit Fed are futile — receive no publicity, never get out of committee
- What is there to investigate? Must assume Fed doing exactly what it says, in total compliance with law
- Minor improprieties might be discovered, but **"Federal Reserve is the world's largest and most successful scam"** — visible without investigators
- **Danger of audit proposal**: provides excuse to delay serious action for years while audit ongoing
- Would give monetary technicians opportunity for "smoke screen of verbiage and confusing statistics"
- By time fourteen volumes appear, public intimidated and fatigued
- **Bottom line: we don't need bill to audit the Fed — need one to abolish it**

### A Plan for Eliminating the Fed

- Simply rescinding Federal Reserve Act would create overnight chaos — play into globalists' hands
- American people would welcome IMF/World Bank "rescue" — back to Pessimistic Scenario
- **Safe passage requires steps**:

**1. Repeal legal-tender laws**
- Government continues accepting FRNs for taxes, but everyone else free to accept, reject, or discount
- Only fiat money needs threat of imprisonment — honest money doesn't
- Private institutions free to innovate, compete with any medium of exchange (Green Stamps, Disney coupons, Bank-of-America Notes)
- Only requirement: faithful fulfillment of contract

**2. Freeze present supply of FRNs** (except for step 11)

**3. Define "real" dollar in precious-metal content**
- Preferably historical: 371.25 grains of silver
- Could be another weight or even another metal

**4. Establish gold as auxiliary monetary reserve**
- Substituted for silver at free-market ratio (not fixed-price ratio)
- Gold may substitute for silver only at market ratio — **only silver is foundation for dollar**

**5. Restore free coinage at U.S. Mint**
- Issue silver "dollars" and gold "pieces"
- Coins defined by metal content only
- Dollars, half-dollars, quarter-dollars, dimes derived only from metal brought to Mint by private parties (not Treasury's supply, reserved for step 6)

**6. Pay off national debt with FRNs created for that purpose**
- Creating money without backing forbidden by Constitution
- However, when no one forced to accept FRNs as legal tender, no longer official U.S. money
- FRNs become "government scrip" — utility determined by usefulness in paying taxes and public anticipation of exchange for real money later
- Decision to redeem government bonds with FRNs already made when bonds issued — we're "playing out the hand"
- Choice is when: now or later (inflation will repudiate debt gradually if bonds stand)

**7. Pledge government's gold and silver hoard** (except military stockpile) as backing for all FRNs in circulation
- Denationalization of these assets long overdue — at various times illegal for Americans to own gold
- Amount taken from private sector should be returned as matter of principle
- Government has no use for gold/silver except supporting money supply

**8. Determine weight of all government gold/silver, calculate total value in real (silver) dollars**

**9. Determine number of all FRNs in circulation, calculate real-dollar value of each**
- Divide value of precious metals by number of Notes

**10. Retire all FRNs by offering to exchange for dollars at calculated ratio**
- Enough gold/silver to redeem every FRN in circulation

**11. Convert all contracts based on FRNs to dollars** using same exchange ratio
- Includes mortgages and government bonds
- Monetary values in debt obligations converted on same basis and time as currency

**12. Issue Silver Certificates**
- As Treasury redeems FRNs for dollars, recipients get option of coins or 100% backed Treasury Certificates
- These become new paper currency

**13. Abolish the Federal Reserve System**
- Could continue as check clearing-house (not as central bank)
- Banks presently owning Fed allowed to continue that service
- Must no longer receive tax subsidies, competition must be allowed
- Federal Reserve System as chartered by Congress must be abolished

**14. Introduce free banking**
- Banks deregulated, cut loose from taxpayer protection — no more bailouts
- FDIC and government "insurance" agencies phased out, functions to real insurance companies
- **Banks required to keep 100% reserves for demand deposits** (contractual obligation)
- All time deposits presented as CEs (Certificates of Deposit) — depositor fully informed money invested, must wait specified time
- Competition ensures institutions serving customers best will prosper; others fall by wayside

**15. Reduce size and scope of government**
- No solution possible under socialism
- Government limited to protection of life, liberty, property — nothing more
- Elimination of socialist-oriented programs infesting federal bureaucracy
- Sell all assets not related to primary function of protection
- Privately sub-contract as many services as possible
- Greatly reduce and simplify taxes

**16. Restore national independence**
- Similar restraint at international level — reverse programs leading to disarmament and economic interdependence
- Get US out of UN and UN out of US — just the beginning
- Rescind hundreds of treaties and administrative agreements
- A few constructive and mutually beneficial, but great majority must go — avoid being engulfed in global tyranny

### Measuring the Size of the Hangover

- **September 30, 1993 data** (illustrative purposes):
  - Government silver: 30,200,000 troy ounces
  - At 371.25 grains per dollar (.77344 troy oz), valued at $39,046,338
  - Gold price: $384.95 FRNs per ounce; silver: $4.99 per ounce; ratio 77-to-1
  - Gold supply: 261,900,000 ounces; value at 77x weight = $26,073,517,000
  - Combined silver and gold value: $26,112,563,338
  - M1 money supply: 1,103,700,000,000 FRNs
  - National debt: 4,395,700,000,000 FRNs
  - Total to redeem: 5,499,400,000,000 FRNs
- **Bottom line**: each FRN worth 0.0047 silver dollar — **one silver dollar = 213 FRNs**

### Bad, But Not That Bad

- Sounds worse than it is — new dollars will have more purchasing power than old
- Coins will play larger role in everyday transactions — nickel phone call and ten-cent cigar return
- Any quantity of gold/silver works as foundation — if quantity low, value per unit high
- Coins solve the problem — pennies for coffee, one mill (tenth of cent) for phone call
- New small-denomination tokens fill that need
- Monetary supply of gold/silver would increase in response to free-market demand
- **Natural equilibrium reached** — as always happened in past; tokens phased out
- **Transition inflation will occur but significantly different from fiat-money inflation**:
  1. Caused by natural economic forces seeking equilibrium, not politicians/bankers manipulating economy
  2. Instead of harming nation/destroying economy, part of healing process leading to prosperity
  3. Less severe than what we'll experience if we don't make transition
  4. Built-in termination point — when human effort to mine gold/silver equals effort to create things gold/silver can buy, money supply ceases expansion, inflation stops
- Hangover gone — prices begin gradual descent as technology improves production efficiency
- **Result: honest money supply, government with no national debt, economy without inflation**

### Practical Considerations

- Could redefine new dollar with smaller silver quantity, continue using present coinage — but creates headaches after transition (coinage too cheap)
- Now is time to do it right — **original value of silver dollar determined after centuries of trial and error**
- Banks must distinguish between demand deposits (100% reserves, coins/Treasury Certificates in vault, not loaned) and time deposits (invested, cannot be withdrawn immediately)
- **Effect on banking will be enormous**: must pay higher interest to attract investment capital, trim overhead, eliminate plush expenses, tighten profit margins
- Used to offer "free" services paid from interest on customers' demand deposits — now must charge for checking and safe storage
- Efficiency will improve — "free" services actually paid out of interest earned on customers' demand deposits

### Some Bad News and Some Good

- Freeze on money supply may trigger stock market panic, business community alarm
- Stock prices could tumble, weak banks close (no bailouts), unemployment may worsen temporarily
- Those on free ride now must walk, push, or pay their way
- Masses on welfare won't give up checks and food stamps quietly
- Media will fan flames, "Cabal will be at every switch to derail the train"
- **Moment of greatest danger** — people could tire of journey, long for captivity, head back to "slave pits of Pharaoh"

**But most problems temporary**:
- Only during transition period
- As soon as free coinage available and demand visible, miners and jewelers add precious metal to nation's monetary stock
- Foreigners add to inflow; old silver/gold coins reappear
- Quickly, monetary supply increases, per-unit value drops to natural equilibrium
- **Four ways this inflation differs from fiat-money inflation** (detailed above)
- After storm: America will have honest money, no national debt, economy without inflation

### Precautions for Realistic Scenario

- Transition won't be orderly — entire system could collapse, including international structure at UN
- Primary concern becomes basic survival if full collapse occurs
- **Economic chaos and civil disorder needn't lead to world government** — if enough informed people in right positions provide leadership at critical moment
- Groups of enlightened individuals prepared in advance could move into power vacuum
- May sound like pessimistic scenario, but theoretically possible — shouldn't hope for it, but should prepare

### How to Prepare Financially

**1. Get out of debt** — mortgage on home logical exception if price right; business borrowing exception if sound plan; no speculative investments with borrowed money

**2. Pick sound bank** — maintain accounts at several institutions; don't keep over $100,000 in any one (FDIC limits); some offer private insurance

**3. Diversify investments** — blue ribbon, over-the-counter, growth, income, large, small, mutuals, bonds, real estate, bullion coins, mining stock, tangibles; industries doing well in hard times (not gambling, alcohol, escapist entertainment); study fields and companies; personal knowledge indispensable

**4. Avoid most recent "best" performers** — historical track records irrelevant to future performance; may be overpriced now

**5. When investing in coins, avoid high numismatic value** — unless prepared to become expert; same for diamonds, art, collectibles; stay with what you know

**6. Maintain cash stash, including old silver coins** — enough for family necessities for two months; coins for severe/prolonged conditions; no "correct" quantity (personal judgment and financial ability)

### Profiting from Disaster

- **Adlai Stevenson**: "exciting prospect that we can turn this calamity to our advantage"
- Can actually profit from coming collapse
- Hundreds of books/newsletters on getting rich while others destroyed
- Some pitch "how to cash in on environmental-industry boom" or "fortune on downfall of America"
- **Opportunities exist for profit based on realistic appraisal of trends** — but depend on market-timing decisions
- Must know industries, monitor daily market shifts, reach conclusions ahead of crowd, be right
- Most investors unprepared — must depend on professionals (same experts encouraging investment in these enterprises)
- If investment profitable, analyst receives income; if sour, analyst still receives income

**Problem with "profit-from-crash" concept**:
- Helps make matters worse by finding clever ways to avoid/profit from inflation instead of stopping it
- Those gaining from inflation not likely to resist — may become ardent supporters
- **Henry Hazlitt**: "There is no safe hedge against inflation except to stop it"

### An Educational Crusade

- **Best investment**: finance educational crusade
- Americans have had nation stolen because they didn't understand what was happening
- No hope while condition remains
- **Starting point**: awakening of America

**Tasks**:

**1. Become self-informed** — major commitment of time and money for books, recordings, seminars

**2. Become a pamphleteer** — develop mailing list of receptive friends; send monthly informative material (not too long)

